{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo_tutorials/pullrequests/265/comments/10222710.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo_tutorials/diff/0xb000/gazebo_tutorials:ba451e2ced33..acc8597c61c7?path=wide_angle_camera%2Ftutorial.md"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo_tutorials/pull-requests/265/_/diff#comment-10222710"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 265, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo_tutorials/pullrequests/265.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo_tutorials/pull-requests/265"}}, "title": "Wideanglecamera"}, "content": {"raw": "The camera sways in a slow motion if you drop it in a weird way. Adding realistic inertia values helps:\n\n~~~\n      <inertial>\n        <mass>0.1</mass>\n        <inertia>\n          <ixx>0.000166667</ixx>\n          <iyy>0.000166667</iyy>\n          <izz>0.000166667</izz>\n        </inertia>\n      </inertial>\n~~~\n\nFor reference, I used [this](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_moments_of_inertia) to calculate it. I'll change this for the normal camera too.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The camera sways in a slow motion if you drop it in a weird way. Adding realistic inertia values helps:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>      <span class=\"nt\">&lt;inertial&gt;</span>\n        <span class=\"nt\">&lt;mass&gt;</span>0.1<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/mass&gt;</span>\n        <span class=\"nt\">&lt;inertia&gt;</span>\n          <span class=\"nt\">&lt;ixx&gt;</span>0.000166667<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/ixx&gt;</span>\n          <span class=\"nt\">&lt;iyy&gt;</span>0.000166667<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/iyy&gt;</span>\n          <span class=\"nt\">&lt;izz&gt;</span>0.000166667<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/izz&gt;</span>\n        <span class=\"nt\">&lt;/inertia&gt;</span>\n      <span class=\"nt\">&lt;/inertial&gt;</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>For reference, I used <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_moments_of_inertia\" rel=\"nofollow\">this</a> to calculate it. I'll change this for the normal camera too.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2015-09-24T20:46:20.880043+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "inline": {"to": 59, "from": null, "outdated": false, "path": "wide_angle_camera/tutorial.md"}, "updated_on": "2015-09-24T20:46:20.885960+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 10222710}